{
  "stem": "13911.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the Russians came in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then everything went peacefully.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It-- I mean, except-- for me-- probably, my father didn't like it-- when you take away a business that you built all your life and this is your livelihood, you know?",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But to me, Russian school was terrific, because Russians, they had holidays, parties, dancing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Every so often there was-- and I was-- we were four girls and four boys-- dancers.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were always-- in Russia, you know, this is the way they kept the people happy.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There's always music, the accordion, and you dance.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And you sing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You know, it was a-- [LAUGHS] --and so I would dance away my-- I-- I loved it, the two years in Russian school.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But then, after two years-- and then, you know, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This is like a political thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I don't know how much I can talk.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I could talk for days and never end.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You see, when-- when the Russians occupied this part, the Germans-- the western part, all the Jews-- I believe that all the Jews came running to the east.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were afraid to stay with the Germans.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it became so congested.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was no place to cope.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was no place-- impossible to cope with such a volume of-- of people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So the Russians sent them to Siberia, those-- the refugees.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We stayed in our home.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the refugees were all sent to Siberia, which a lot-- a lot of my friends-- that became friends later.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And actually, if you see, from Polish people who survived with a mother, a father, an uncle-- because we-- it was very seldom that you survive with a sibling.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But those in Siberia, they had a very hard time there.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
